title.children: India fight back on second morning of WTC final after Smith brings up ton

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Oh disaster for Australia! The bowling change works for India and Steve Smith has to go after playing on. He looked to drive away from his body and was a bit lazy with the shot perhaps? He goes for 121 off 268 balls and Australia are suddenly 6 down and there are two new batters at the crease.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: SMITH HAS TO GO!

children.content: Oh disaster for Australia!
The bowling change works for India and Steve Smith has to go after playing on.
(Getty Images)

He goes for 121 off 268 balls and Australia are suddenly 6 down and there are two new batters at the crease.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Shubman Gill takes the catch at second slip and it flew hard to him. Green has to go for 6 off 7 balls. Green didn't show much footwork there, tried to drive, away from his body, the ball flew off the edge of the bat but it was a loose shot. India just might be feeling like they're getting some mometum here.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: EDGED! OUT! GREEN HAS TO GO!

children.content: Shubman Gill takes the catch at second slip and it flew hard to him.
Green has to go for 6 off 7 balls.
(Getty Images)
Green didn't show much footwork there, tried to drive, away from his body, the ball flew off the edge of the bat but it was a loose shot.
India just might be feeling like they're getting some mometum here.
(AP)

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Oh that's a shame for Travis Head, just a handful of runs shy of his best Test score. He tried to hook, got a bit of glove on it and it was easy pickings for Bharat behind the stumps. It's a good ball from Siraj, who is cockahoop and screaming in delight, as is Kohli, who has found that trampoline that he was on for much of the first two sessions yesterday. It's a terrific innings through from Head, who gets a standing ovation as he walks off. He's out for 163 from 174 balls. Siraj gets his man. Finally.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: GOT HIM! TRAVIS HEAD HAS TO GO!

children.content: Oh that's a shame for Travis Head, just a handful of runs shy of his best Test score.

It's a terrific innings through from Head, who gets a standing ovation as he walks off.
